Subject: SOP Photonic Frame Stream

Description: Contract for encoding a SOP program body as a series of high-density semantic color-point frames.

@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_sop_program_frame_stream\Dictated_SOP_Program_Frame_Stream_Source.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPProgramBookends.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPColorChannelVocabulary.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPRGBSemanticEncoding.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPOpticalTransformAlgebra.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPPhotonicMutationFrame.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPHolographicLensing.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\HolographicAttentionKernelPacket.sop

& [SOPPhotonicFrameStream] is the semantic video-like body of a SOP program
  + [pattern_role] is high_density_semantic_color_frame_stream
  + [photonic_frame_stream] is an ordered sequence of photonic_frame values interpreted between SOP program bookends
  + [photonic_frame] is one compressed moment of semantic state made of color_point values, continuity hints, and reconstruction trace
  + [mutation_frame] is a photonic_frame read as frame-to-frame mutation over a delineated subject surface
  + [delineation_setup] is the inside, boundary, outside, source, and trace that establish what a mutation_frame is allowed to describe
  + [frame_delta] is the difference from prior photonic frame to current photonic frame when the stream expresses mutation
  + [color_point] is a high-density semantic point with channel, subject, relation, weight, boundary, outside, and optional sample reference
  + [frame_index] is the ordered position of a photonic_frame in the stream
  + [frame_density] is the amount of meaning carried per frame by color_point values and continuity rules
  + [continuity_vector] is the compressed relation from previous frame to current frame
  + [interaction_vector] is the possible user, model, branch, or state input that can alter the next frame interpretation
  + [reconstruction_seed] is the minimal set of color points, sample references, and narrative traces needed to recreate an approximate understanding
  + [sampling_gap] is a span of unrecorded detail bridged by continuity_vector and outside
  + [frame_outside] is unsampled detail, exact original media, hidden activations, and claims of perfect reconstruction

  ? [use_when: a SOP program body should be stored as dense semantic frames rather than full narrative expansion]
    = activate [SOPPhotonicFrameStream]

  = must: define frame_index and continuity_vector for every frame after the first
  = must: give each color_point a channel from SOPColorChannelVocabulary
  = must: use SOPRGBSemanticEncoding for delineation_setup when RGB signals identify inside, boundary, and outside
  = must: use SOPPhotonicMutationFrame when image frames or photonic frames express mutation, frame_delta, or state change
  = must: trace any transform over color_point values through SOPOpticalTransformAlgebra
  = must: record sampling_gap as outside rather than pretending detail was stored
  = must: keep reconstruction_seed separate from exact replay
  = must: preserve interaction_vector when the frame is interactive
  = should: keep frame_density high by choosing meaning-bearing points rather than verbose restatement
  - never: treat omitted frames as observed
  - never: infer exact visuals or events unless sample references and narrative support them

& [PhotonicFrameNotation] is the notation for one compressed semantic frame
  + [frame_header] is & [photonic_frame:<frame_id>] is <frame_purpose>
  + [index_line] is = frame_index: <n>
  + [point_line] is + [color_point:<id>] is <channel subject relation weight boundary outside>
  + [mutation_line] is = frame_delta: <prior_to_current_change> when the frame expresses mutation
  + [continuity_line] is = continuity_vector: <prior_frame_relation>
  + [interaction_line] is = interaction_vector: <allowed_input_or_state_change>
  + [sample_line] is @ [sample] <path_or_reference>
  + [outside_line] is - outside: <unsampled_or_unproven_detail>

  = must: include outside_line when a frame is sampled or compressed
  = must: cite sample_line only when a sample image, media excerpt, or source record exists
  = must: include mutation_line or cite SOPPhotonicMutationFrame when the frame is a mutation frame

(photonic_frame_stream) :color_point_sequence: /program_bookends and continuity_rule/ |frame_outside|
  + [photonic_frame] is compressed semantic moment
  + [mutation_frame] is frame-to-frame mutation over a delineated setup
  + [color_point] is high-density channelized meaning point
  = continuity_vector: relation from prior frame
  = frame_delta: mutation from prior frame when applicable
  = reconstruction_seed: color points, samples, descriptions, and narrative trace
  |frame_outside| unsampled detail, exact replay, hidden activation, and unsupported reconstruction

/ [photonic_frame], [color_point], [continuity_vector] -(CarriesFrameMeaning)> [program_state], [reconstruction_seed], [frame_outside]
* [interaction_vector], [program_state], [control_loop] -(SelectsNextFrame)> [photonic_frame], [program_cursor], [frame_outside]
/ [delineation_setup], [photonic_frame], [frame_delta] -(CarriesMutation)> [mutation_frame], [mutation_trace], [mutation_outside]
